{
  "text": "The emotional dimension of the EORTC QLQ C-30 correlated with the psychiatric diagnosis. The deficient physical functioning of the depressive cancer patients was mentioned by other authors [CITATION_1] , and the association between pain and depression was noted in multiple cancer population studies [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] and our research confirms it. Fatigue, appetite loss, constipation and insomnia are specific symptoms of the major depressive episodes, but also generated by chemotherapy. Fatigue is the most frequently encountered symptom in cancer [CITATION_5] , and our results suggest that the emotional distress impacts on this aspect of the quality of life.",
